{"block1":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Back pain is one of the most common conditions that people suffer from. As well as the pain itself, it can cause severe disruption to your daily routine. Most people take basic pain medication for the condition and wait for it to simply pass. Of course, back pain can always come back and often it does. If you read about back pain, you will discover that there is no actual proof what causes back pain, but it is actually a symptom of another condition.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/portrait-of-a-doctor-examining-a-man.jpg\" class=\"img_right \" alt=\"portrait of a doctor examining a man\" style=\"float: right; padding: 8px; padding-right: 0;\" \/><\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have slept on a bed that is uncomfortable or was too hard, your back may be sore, but the pain may disappear&nbsp;within a few days. However, if you have had back pain for many weeks, or even months, you should consult your doctor, as there could be something seriously wrong with your back.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Back pain can result from&nbsp;many different factors.&nbsp;I know for a fact that if I haven&#39;t been paying attention to my posture, especially in front of the computer, I will have back pain later in the evening.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Another cause of&nbsp;back pain can be lifting heavy items, where you may have&nbsp;hurt a muscle in the process. I have also been told that if you are overweight and have&nbsp;weak stomach muscles, this can cause&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/www.mayoclinic.org\/symptom-checker\/low-back-pain-adult\/related-factors\/itt-20009075\"  >lower back pain<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have never had back pain before, know that it can be very painful and even disabling.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are also many medical conditions that can cause back pain, especially if you have a problem with one of your organs. There could even be something wrong with your spine, which is why it is always wise to consult a professional when it comes to finding solutions to relieve your back pain. It makes sense to find the cause of the pain before trtying to treat it.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Anyone can suffer from back pain, whether you are fat, thin, tall, short or athletic. Pain is pain and it does not discriminate. There are many <a href=\"http:\/\/joints.center\/joints-information\/knowing-causes-pain-joint\/\"  >causes of back pain<\/a>&nbsp;and these can differ from person to person, ranging from mild to severe pain. Either way, in most cases the pain will disappear after a while, all on its own.<\/p>\r\n"}